10:16 AM Defendant Vincent K Holmes in court, in custody.  Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Vincent K Holmes.  Attorney Molly M Schmidt in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Court informs parties it was just in receipt of a motion to dismiss count 3 of the criminal complaint at 8:45 am this morning.  
Attorney Gutierrez states he did send a copy to Attorney Schmidt yesterday when he e-filed it and does note he was just appointed on Friday.  
Court conducts colloquy with the parties in regards to proceeding on the motion.  
Attorney Schmidt states she is prepared to move forward on the motion today.  
The Court proceeds to arguments.  
Attorney Gutierrez moves to dismiss count 3 of the criminal complaint and presents arguments.
Attorney Schmidt presents arguments in support of count 3.  
Response argument by Attorney Gutierrez.
Response argument by Attorney Schmidt.
For all the reasons stated on the record, the Court denies the motion to dismiss Count 3.  

Defense requests a preliminary hearing and the Court conducts a hearing: 
Officer Jason Trimborn of the City of Waukesha Police Department, sworn in and testifies on direct by Attorney Schmidt.
Cross examination by attorney Gutierrez.  
The witness is excused and the State rests.
The Defense rests with no testimony proffered.
The Court deems testimony closed.

The State presents closing arguments and moves for bind over.
The Defense presents closing arguments and objects to bind over.
Court finds probable cause to believe that a felony was committed and binds the defendant over for trial.

Waive reading of Information.
